<br>
Teapray's story does go on. It is played. There is a significant difference there. Many things can be played. And it can generate wonderful situations, for roleplay, as long as all involved accept the challenge, and roleplay it, rather than going ooc and mouthing off.<br>
<br>
In my eyes, it is the pervect example why rules can never truly work for rp. Any rules set would have made this tale impossible. But it is not. It is possible, and can generate interesting roleplay. That is, as long as there arent dozens of ogre-highelf pairs. And as long as the players are willing to accept that their characters might be ridiculed, scorned, and left out of groups, because of their 'love'. <p>Silenae Do'Bauthin<br><br>
